com.yworks.yfiles.layout.hierarchic

Class TypeBasedDrawingDistanceCalculator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.layout.hierarchic.TypeBasedDrawingDistanceCalculator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDrawingDistanceCalculator

    public class TypeBasedDrawingDistanceCalculator
extends Object
implements IDrawingDistanceCalculator
    This class is a IDrawingDistanceCalculator implementation that returns the minimum distances for each kind of node pair based on their type as returned by Type.

        Description copied from interface: IDrawingDistanceCalculator
        Main interface method called by INodePlacer instances to determine the minimum distance between Nodes of same layer.
        Specified by:
        getMinDistance in interface IDrawingDistanceCalculator
        Parameters:
        graph - the input graph
        layer - the ILayer object that will be used during subsequent calls
        ldp - the ILayoutDataProvider implementation which provides access to the INodeData and IEdgeData instances
        left - the left of the two Nodes whose minimum distance is to be determined or null if only the left border of the right Node is of interest
        right - the right of the two Nodes whose minimum distance is to be determined or null if only the right border of the left Node is of interest
        Returns:
        the minimum distance between two Nodes of the same layer

      • getMinimumFirstSegmentLength

        public double getMinimumFirstSegmentLength()
        Gets the minimum length of the first segment of the edge path (at the source node).

        The minimum length should be greater than 0.

        If the value is 0.0d the first segment does not need to be orthogonal.

        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the minimum length of the first segment is negative
        Default Value:
        The default value is 15.0d.
        Returns:
        the minimum length of the first segment
        See Also:
        setMinimumFirstSegmentLength(double)

      • isCompactionEnabled

        public boolean isCompactionEnabled()
        Gets whether or not the compaction option is enabled.
         
        This option is automatically set by the layout algorithm if option NodeCompaction or LabelCompactionEnabled is enabled.
        Default Value:
        The default value is false. Compaction is disabled.
        Returns:
        true if compaction is enabled, false otherwise
